# GDP Growth Analysis 🌍

A Python data analysis tool that finds the fastest growing
economies in the world using real World Bank data.

## What it does
- Loads real GDP data from the internet
- Cleans and filters out regional groupings
- Calculates GDP growth % between any two years
- Ranks all countries
- Shows a bar chart of top 10

## How to run
1. Install pandas and matplotlib
   pip install pandas matplotlib

2. Run the script
   python gdp_analysis.py

## Key findings (2010-2023)
- Fastest growing: Ethiopia, Somalia, Bangladesh
- India rank: #40 with 69% growth
- China: #10 with 134% growth

## Tools used
- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- World Bank GDP Dataset

